Research shows consuming Omega 6s from seed oils can:

Increase the risk of all-cause mortality by 35% when replacing saturated fat.

Induce obesity and diabetes, and alter the regulation of the brain’s hunger

signaling in the hypothalamus.

Lead to higher rates of mood disorders and depression in young people.

Reduce sperm count, quality and mobility, and testicular volume.

Promote inflammation in joints.

Increase the risk of severe asthma in children.

Significantly decrease working memory and synapse health.
